*Project Name: Star Curtain Project (SCP)
*Project Number: BACKROOMS-BS-SCP
*Project Classification: Public
*Initiating Organizations: Major Explorer Group, Star Worshippers
*Initiating Date: 2023/08/23

==I. Project Overview and Establishment Purpose==
The Star Curtain Project is a cross-level sharing project based on the current survival status of Backrooms wanderers, with the rare special resource Bottled Starlight as its core carrier. In the initial stage, the project takes safety, mutual assistance, sharing and sustainability as its core concepts. It aims to develop a exclusive starlight recipe system for the wanderers in the Backrooms, build multiple sharing systems including safe sharing and spiritual mutual assistance, realize efficient sharing of Bottled Starlight within a controllable range, alleviate survival anxiety in the Backrooms, and build a stable and mutual-aid community across the entire Backrooms.

==II. Overall Project Architecture==
With the recipe application of Bottled Starlight as the core, supplemented by relevant resource storage management and supporting facility construction, the Star Curtain Project constructs a three-dimensional engineering architecture of "R&D - Storage - Service", which fully supports the survival needs of wanderers.
<tabber>
|-|Starlight Recipes=
<p>◈ The Starlight Recipe system was jointly developed by the Major Explorer Group and the Star Worshippers. According to the environmental characteristics of different levels in the Backrooms, it provides cooking and consumption schemes of Bottled Starlight adapted to various scenarios, maximizing the beneficial effects of Bottled Starlight. Meanwhile, the R&D team will continuously collect consumption feedback from wanderers on all levels, and constantly adjust and update the recipe according to actual experience, so that the starlight recipes meet the physical tolerance of the vast majority of wanderers and reduce the threshold of use.</p>
<p>◈ In terms of content, starlight recipes are divided into three grades: basic, advanced and special. Each grade contains dozens of cooking methods for Bottled Starlight, and gives a brief introduction to each cooking method, including but not limited to sections such as ingredient acquisition, preparation method, consumption dosage, beneficial effects, negative effects and applicable scenarios. For special groups such as the elderly, children, pregnant women, the sick and the disabled, exclusive formulas are customized in the recipe to fit the physical tolerance of different groups and effectively protect the physical and mental state of every wanderer.</p>
<p>◈ Among the recipes, the basic grade is for daily supply of ordinary wanderers. The production process is simple and convenient, can be quickly produced in batches to meet the basic survival consumption of a large range of people, and is suitable for conventional levels with stable living environment and low danger; the advanced grade focuses on the repair and conditioning of wanderers' physical and mental health. It is usually used to treat the spiritual trauma of wanderers, alleviate negative emotions such as fear and anxiety, and also can cure diseases and wounds for wanderers; the special grade is usually only used for wanderers' self-protection in extreme environments, helping wanderers evacuate and avoid danger.</p>
<p>◈ The recipe data will be uniformly archived and sorted by the Major Explorer Group, and distributed to service stations on all levels for wanderers to collect by themselves; meanwhile, the Major Explorer Group will timely replace the recipe data in the stations to avoid outdated information misleading wanderers.</p>
|-|Shared Starlight Warehouses=
<p>◈ The Shared Starlight Warehouse is the physical supporting project of the starlight recipes, which usually exists as service stations on various levels. It is used to store starlight resources and recipe raw materials for all wanderers to access and use.</p>
<p>◈ According to the safety assessment of each level in the Backrooms, the Star Curtain Project has set up multiple Shared Starlight Warehouses, their locations cover but are not limited to levels with a large number of wanderers. The stations are usually located in areas with open vision and convenient access, after completion, multiple guide signs will be marked nearby to help foreign wanderers quickly find the station location. In addition, each shared warehouse will build a exclusive protective structure according to the environmental characteristics of the level, so as to maintain the safety of internal resources and personnel.</p>
<p>◈ The interior of the Shared Starlight Warehouse is mainly divided into three areas: storage area, sharing area and cooking area. Normally, each station is equipped with five to six permanent personnel to carry out daily patrols, regularly check the integrity of protective facilities, timely repair damaged positions, and prevent entities or lawbreakers from breaking into the station to destroy or steal materials.</p>
<p>◈ The number of Shared Starlight Warehouse stations will continue to grow, and will achieve coverage of most well-known levels across the entire Backrooms in the near future. Real-time information interconnection is maintained between all stations. If a certain station has insufficient material reserves, neighboring stations will quickly complete material allocation and replenishment, ensuring that there will be no shortage of resource supply in stations on all levels.</p>
</tabber>

==III. Project Implementation System==
The implementation system of the Star Curtain Project is divided into four levels: planning layer, resource layer, execution layer and support layer, it is promoted as a whole from top to bottom, and each level performs its own duties to complete the entire implementation process of the Star Curtain Project.
<tabber>
|-|Planning Layer=
<p>◈ The planning layer is composed of members of the Major Explorer Group and the Star Worshippers, and is the top-level department in the implementation system of the Star Curtain Project.</p>
<p>◈ The planning layer will conduct a comprehensive investigation on the overall status of all known level stations, count data such as the number of wanderers, existing material reserves, environmental hazard level and entity threat level in each region, and formulate phased promotion plans that fit the actual situation based on the current status, ensuring that every step of the plan is implemented in line with the actual survival of the level, and will not be out of practice and difficult to implement.</p>
<p>◈ Meanwhile, the planning layer will regularly hold the plenary meeting for negotiation on the implementation plan of the Star Curtain Project, referred to as the Full Implementation Conference, and call on personnel from all levels to participate in the meeting. The Full Implementation Conference will summarize the progress of the plan in each participant's jurisdiction, discuss and evaluate the reasonable demands and improvement suggestions put forward by grassroots wanderers, and optimize the implementation plan. The meeting will also discuss the next stage's recipe update direction, resource collection goals, station addition planning, etc., and reach a unified consensus on cross-level resource allocation, personnel cooperation and other matters.</p>
<p>◈ The planning layer is also responsible for approving the work results of other levels.</p>
|-|Resource Layer=
<p>◈ The resource layer is led by the Major Explorer Group, and is mainly responsible for collecting Bottled Starlight, counting resource consumption and other work.</p>
<p>◈ The resource layer accurately grasps the change of resource stock by regularly calculating daily material consumption, so as to determine the intensity and direction of subsequent collection work. After that, the resource layer will arrange professional search teams to go to various levels to carry out resource search and collection, and check entity traces and level traps on the search route in advance, to maximize the personal safety of collection personnel when working out in the field.</p>
<p>◈ The resource layer formulates standardized storage and protection specifications to strictly control the physical integrity of Bottled Starlight stored in the warehouse, and provide resource support for subsequent station deployment. At the same time, the resource layer will also coordinate and handle matters related to resource loss, conduct unified harmless treatment of invalid and unusable Bottled Starlight, establish an emergency resource reserve warehouse, separately store a fixed proportion of high-quality starlight resources, and immediately mobilize reserve resources for rescue when large-scale levels face material shortage.</p>
<p>◈ In addition, the resource layer will simultaneously carry out raw material grading, divide consumption grades according to safety degree and rarity index, provide standardized raw materials for recipe research and development and distribution supply, ensure sustainable supply of ingredients, and distribute resources in order of priority according to the material needs fed back by each level station.</p>
|-|Execution Layer=
<p>◈ The execution layer is mainly composed of members of the Major Explorer Group and the Star Worshippers, and is the most indispensable level in the implementation system of the Star Curtain Project.</p>
<p>◈ The execution layer constructs Bottled Starlight service stations on various levels according to the plan, builds station buildings, material storage points and rest areas in accordance with unified construction standards, and does basic protection against entity threats and environmental hazards according to the environmental conditions of the level, ensuring that the station can be put into use stably for a long time, and appropriately expand or reduce the scale of the station according to the size of resident wanderers.</p>
<p>◈ The execution layer undertakes the distribution of starlight materials. According to the material quota issued by the planning layer, it regularly delivers Bottled Starlight and finished starlight recipe dishes to the corresponding level stations to supplement the station material inventory, ensuring that wanderers can get the supplies they need at any time. In addition, it has formulated orderly material application rules, set a daily collection limit for a single person, and made simple registration of personnel information during the application process, which is convenient for subsequent statistics of material consumption speed in each level.</p>
<p>◈ The execution layer will also help wanderers who are new to starlight recipes, and explain each dish in detail for these groups. At the same time, it collects the opinions and suggestions of wanderers on all levels on material distribution, station services and other aspects, sorts and summarizes them and reports them layer by layer, assisting the upper level to adjust the service methods and make the execution work more in line with the actual needs of wanderers.</p>
<p>◈ In addition, the R&D department of the execution layer will continuously promote the update of starlight recipes, and regularly modify and improve the recipe content based on the opinions and suggestions of wanderers.</p>
|-|Support Layer=
<p>◈ As the name implies, the support layer is responsible for various support work. It is mainly composed of Star Worshippers. It will record the behavioral characteristics and frequent levels of various entities, sort and compile them into manuals and distribute them to stations on all levels, so that all personnel can identify dangers and prepare in advance; support work also includes maintaining the safety and order of public areas of levels, cleaning hidden small dangerous hazards, and reducing the possibility of wanderers being attacked in daily activities.</p>
<p>◈ The support layer summarizes rescue skills for dangerous scenarios on various levels, and regularly organizes support personnel to carry out practical exercises to improve the rescue ability in emergency situations, and save the life and health of trapped wanderers to the greatest extent. Secondly, it will provide long-term psychological counseling and spiritual companionship for rescued wanderers who have suffered severe mental trauma, gradually helping them get rid of the shadow of fear and readapt to survival in the Backrooms.</p>
<p>◈ The support layer also formulates the general code of conduct for the Star Curtain Project. For undesirable phenomena such as resource competition and illegal occupation of shared materials that occur in some levels, the support layer will discuss restraint management methods against the general code of conduct, standardize the behavior of all participants. If a person refuses to cooperate and repeatedly violates the rules, corresponding disposal will be made in accordance with the established management methods, and their material application permission will be restricted for a period of time. At the same time, it supervises the performance of duties of internal staff of the station, prevents internal personnel from privately occupying shared materials by using their positions, and ensures that every link is fair and rigorous.</p>
<p>◈ The support layer has its exclusive arsenal and medical depot. All kinds of protection and enemy-control equipment are stored in the arsenal to contain hostile entities and respond to sudden threats; the medical depot is used to store various special medicinal agents and diagnosis and treatment equipment, which can quickly treat various injuries and diseases, and provide material support for guarantee and rescue work.</p>
</tabber>

==IV. Expected Project Objectives==
The project plans to complete the research and development of basic starlight recipes in a short term, achieve full coverage of starlight recipe services in core levels, build standardized shared warehouses and distribution system, allowing wanderers to easily obtain safe and effective edible star products and alleviate the shortage of survival resources.

Within five years of the project initiation, it is expected to further expand the starlight recipes, improve the formula system, unlock more exclusive star formulas adapted to various special levels and extreme environments, meet the needs of diverse scenarios, and maximize the practical value of Bottled Starlight. On the other hand, it will conduct experiments on efficient recycling of ingredients to reduce resource competition conflicts as much as possible.

In the long-term planning, ten years after the project initiation, a mature resource recycling model will be established across the entire Backrooms, and resource loss and waste will be minimized, so that limited starlight resources can be sustainably supplied for a long time. At the same time, it will also connect more groups to join the plan, further expand the coverage and influence of the Star Curtain Project, and steadily promote the positive change of the overall living environment in the Backrooms.

